{[%evp 0,6,25,26,19,-8,0,8,28] [#]} 7. f3 $1 {[%cal Gg2g4,Gh2h4] We are preparing a pawn storm and gaining a space advantage on the kingside. Our king will be safe on the f2 square.} (7. g4 $5 {is another way of aggressive play!} Bh7 8. h4 Bd6 9. Nh3 Ne7 {Ambartsumova,K (2418)-Osmak,Y (2452) FIDE Online Arena INT 2024} 10. Rg1 $1 $36 {[%cal Gd1f3,Ye1c1]}) 7... Bd6 {allows us to take control of the center after} (7... Nf6 8. g4 Bh7 9. h4 Bd6 10. Nge2 Qe7 11. Kf2 Na6 12. g5 $1 (12. Bxd6 Qxd6 $11 {Ju,W (2564)-Paehtz,E (2471) Baku AZE 2023}) 12... Nd7 (12... Nh5 $2 13. Bxd6 Qxd6 14. Bh3 $18 {[%cal Re8c8,Re8g8]}) 13. Rc1 $1 {Important move. We delay 0-0-0 and prepare Bh3} Nc7 (13... O-O-O 14. Nxd5 $18) 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Bh3 O-O-O 16. Qg1 $1 $14 {[%cal Gg1g3] A beautiful move. After the exchange of queens, I believe we have better chances on the kingside. Black can't avoid it, as failing to do so would allow Nxd5!, which would be devastating for Black.}) 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 9. e4 $1 Bh7 10. e5 Qb4 11. Qd2 Nd7 12. f4 $14 {According to the engine, the position is close to equal, and to keep that balance, Black needs to play a lot of precise moves.} *

